# Delegation-triage consumer note (Codex / non-Claude drivers)

Generated from the canonical delegation-triage package at `{{PACKAGE_HOME}}` — regenerate via
`python3 install.py codex` when the package moves.

Before delegating work to a Claude executor:

1. Read `{{PACKAGE_HOME}}/ROUTES.md` (task class → model × effort route | fallback) and
   `{{PACKAGE_HOME}}/STATE.md` (active profile, scarcity mode, expiry).
2. Run `python3 {{PACKAGE_HOME}}/check_state.py` — any expired entry is **Unchecked, never
   true**: re-verify it or route on the ROUTES Fallback column.
3. Pick a spawn surface that can actually deliver the route's model × effort pair —
   `{{PACKAGE_HOME}}/CONTRACT.md` §3's table names which knobs each surface can pin. If your
   surface cannot pin effort, state "effort: session-inherited" and treat effort-critical
   routes as fallback cases.
4. State the fit, one line per spawn: agent/type · model · effort (+ how it arises) · surface ·
   task class · why, citing the ROUTES row or W-ID.
5. Rows marked Contested / Conjecture / CANDIDATE / PARKED are probes to run, not priors to
   trust — read the cited W-record in `{{PACKAGE_HOME}}/WARRANTS.md` first.
6. Record outcomes; post-mortems edit the canonical package's surfaces and append to its
   `probes/` in the same pass.
